{
  "stem": "14060.6",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And I do know of a family in another town-- name not to be mentioned because the children are still around-- who were practically chased out of the town after the war because their family put others on the train and put themselves in.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Anyway, even our rabbi who was a very anti-Zionist man, got in on it, and literally he could not return to our town after the war.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "He stayed in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Anyway, these are unfortunate circumstances.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And when people are put to test, a lot of things happen which probably in normal circumstances they would have never done.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Anyway, now the train went for two and a half days.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "We got joined part of the Szombathely ghetto onto the train.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And as we went towards northeast-- it's still in western Hungary-- the Gyor ghetto was also consolidated on the same train.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "So as it went through-- part of the Szombathely ghetto was transferred to the Sopron ghetto, joined up, because there were not enough people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And once they made up a train, they wanted to make it worthwhile.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Gyor ghetto-- so basically, the Western Hungarian corner towards Austria was one deportation train which left on the 4th of July 1944.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The journey-- 4th?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think so, approximately that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the train arrived in Birkenau on-- at approximately 9:00 in the morning on the Shabbat morning, which was the Jewish date of [NON-ENGLISH] the fast day.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But where I want to tell you that people were, were worried if the word Poland was mentioned, that they're getting sent there, is that I remember clearly.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were at 3:00 in the morning in Krakow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I saw the station writing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, I was pushed up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I looked out.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Approximately 8-something-- I don't even know how I know.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
